&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;**This vacancy is for registered Band 5 Nurses - if you are a student nurse, please contact the recruitment team on 0151 529 3030.**&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen at Liverpool University Hospital (Aintree Site) for Registered Nurses to join the welcoming and friendly team of Ward 20.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you want to be part of developing the knowledge, experience and delivering outstanding care on this 33 bedded Diabetes/General Medical ward?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a true professional with the passion to delivering kind and compassionate care? You will work as part of a multidisciplinary team caring for patients with the opportunity to improve and expand on your clinical knowledge.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer rotational posts with a development programme tailored to your individual needs and interests, which include competency training booklets and mentorship / buddy support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracey Evans, Ward Nurse Manager on 0151 529 6494&lt;/p&gt;
